  "prompt": "Do some people not have dandruffs?",
  "response": "Yes, some people do not experience dandruff. Dandruff is a common scalp condition characterized by flaking and sometimes mild itchiness. It is often caused by factors such as:\n\n1. **Seborrheic Dermatitis**: A common skin condition that causes oily, irritated skin and flaking.\n2. **Malassezia**: A yeast-like fungus that can irritate the scalp and increase skin cell turnover.\n3. **Dry Skin**: Can lead to flaking, especially in colder weather.\n4. **Sensitivity to Hair Products**: Certain hair care products can irritate the scalp and cause flaking.\n\nHowever, not everyone is prone to dandruff. People with a balanced scalp microbiome, proper hydration, and appropriate hair care routines may never experience dandruff. Genetics, overall health, and environmental factors also play a role in whether someone develops dandruff or not.",
